    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Stringed instruments that combine six-stringed guitar setups on a lute bowl; later versions had up to 11 strings. They were common in Germany and elsewhere from around 1850. They resemble medieval and Renaissance bass lutes harps.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
